pageContext.description: Exceptionally well cast and preserved. There is a small rounded shoulder on each side just below the stop ridge.
pageContext.surface: Very smooth, shining and even. Metal shows through wear edge. This may have been filed recently.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,Foster Bequest Cat. No. 107,P.C. 68,(15A),No. 15 A is correct in F.B. Cat.
pageContext.remarks: "A printed slip from the sale catalogue of the Borlase Collection attached to this celt bears the words 112 Bronze Paalstab, with excellent patina, said to be Italian. The peculiarly English Type of the specimen however renders this supposition improbable."
